# AI-Assisted React Application Development Report

## Project: J.A.R.V.I.S. — Joint Attack & Response Virtual Intelligence System

## 1. Project Overview

For this assignment, I used AI as a development assistant to help build a React-based cybersecurity dashboard called **J.A.R.V.I.S. (Joint Attack & Response Virtual Intelligence System)**.

The goal of the project was to create a futuristic cybersecurity command center inspired by Tony Stark’s J.A.R.V.I.S. concept. The application combines ideas from both offensive and defensive cybersecurity:

* Attack simulation (Red Team)
* Security monitoring (Blue Team)
* Incident investigation
* Threat intelligence
* Security operations dashboard

The application was designed with a dark futuristic interface, including dashboards, alerts, incidents, threat information, and investigation features.

---

# 2. Prompts Used

## Initial Project Prompt

I first provided AI with a detailed project specification describing the complete vision, features, design requirements, architecture, and technology stack.

The prompt included:

* Project vision and goals
* User interface requirements
* Dashboard layout
* Cybersecurity modules
* Incident management features
* Threat intelligence features
* Recommended React technology stack
* Database and API design
* Future AI assistant capabilities

The purpose of this prompt was to give AI enough context about the application so it could help design and develop features that matched the overall project vision.

---

## Feature Development Prompt

After creating the initial application, I used AI to implement a specific feature:

> "Build a detailed view modal that opens when clicking 'View Details' on incidents, showing full timelines and evidence artifacts."

The goal was to improve the incident investigation workflow.

---

## AI Response / Implementation Summary

AI helped design and implement an incident investigation modal containing:

### Timeline Section

* Chronological incident events
* Severity indicators
* Event timestamps
* Source attribution

### Evidence Section

* Forensic artifacts
* Logs
* Network captures
* Process snapshots
* SHA-256 hashes
* File information
* View/download actions

### MITRE ATT&CK Section

* Attack technique mappings
* Security tactic categories
* Links to MITRE ATT&CK knowledge base

The modal was integrated into the Incidents page so users could select an incident and investigate it in detail.

